sentences.english: Currently I am an international student at Graduate School of Int'l Studies, Korea University, Seoul, Korea.
sentences.chinese: 我目前就读于韩国高丽大学国际研究生院。

sentences.english: You were the dean of the graduate school.
sentences.chinese: 您曾经是研究生院院长。

sentences.english: The shift in attitudes is also apparent in graduate school enrollment.
sentences.chinese: 这种转变在研究生院的招生中也可见一斑。

sentences.english: Wisdom was not at the top of the graduate mountain, but there in the sandpile at nursery school.
sentences.chinese: 智慧不在研究生院的山巅之上，而在幼儿园的沙堆里。

sentences.english: The university 's Graduate School was established in 1950.
sentences.chinese: 1950年，美国英卡奈特大学研究生院正式成立。

sentences.english: Graduate school will always be there.
sentences.chinese: 研究生院永远会在那里。

sentences.english: Chicago has 6 graduate and professional schools of high repute.
sentences.chinese: 芝加哥有6所颇负盛名的研究生院和专业院校。

sentences.english: I had just finished my second year of graduate school.
sentences.chinese: 我才刚刚完成我在研究生院的第二年。

sentences.english: Masters of Applied Arts in Media Arts (MA), Emily Carr University of Art and Design, Vancouver, BC, Canada.
sentences.chinese: 加拿大艾米利卡尔艺术大学，研究生院，媒体艺术。

sentences.english: Heartfelt congratulations on your graduation from the Graduate School.
sentences.chinese: 真心地恭喜你从研究生院毕业。

sentences.english: The Graduate School of Science will admit at most 20 students each for the master's and doctoral programs each year.
sentences.chinese: 理学研究生院每年将最多录取硕士和博士生各20名。

sentences.english: I have strong education , degree from the university , graduate school and the law school.
sentences.chinese: 我有较强的教育，从大学学位，研究生院和法学院。

sentences.english: There's a lot of different graduate schools here.
sentences.chinese: 这儿有许多不同的研究生院。

sentences.english: Other graduate schools are also expecting increases in applicants.
sentences.chinese: 其他研究生院也都预计申请人数会增加。

sentences.english: Sheldon:Not bad-- I, myself, started graduate school at 14.
sentences.chinese: 不错啊，我本人是14岁读的研究生院。
